        <div class="price-desc">Cooktop glass surface · multi-zone induction generator · door glass</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="price-note">Repair-vs-replace math on Gaggenau almost always wins for repair. Against $8,000-$15,000 replacement-unit costs (BO 480 ~$12K, BX 480 ~$15K, DF 480 with custom panel ~$7K, full Vario cooktop installation ~$10K+), even an $880 boiler element swap or a $1,400 cooktop glass replacement is a comparatively small expenditure to recover another 5-10 years of service life. We tell you the math before any parts get ordered. BSH parts cross-compatibility with Bosch/Siemens shared components sometimes accelerates lead time when cross-references apply.</p>
