<!-- 07 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">07, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Gaggenau jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three representative service calls — model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Gaggenau service.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Gaggenau BO 480 combi-steam oven, Bel Air</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Owner noticed inconsistent steam injection during steam-only cycles — bread coming out unevenly proofed, occasional steam visible escaping the upper door edge during run. Unit was 6 years old, in the 2018 production cohort.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Classic 2016-2020 BO 480 door hinge assembly failure pattern. Door not closing fully flush against the seal, confirmed with a feeler gauge — seal compression uneven across the perimeter. Hinge spring and pivot bearing checked: pivot bearing wear evident, spring tension below spec.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Hinge assembly replacement with OEM Gaggenau part (in stock on the truck). Verified seal compression uniform across all four edges after install. Ran test steam cycle, confirmed normal steam injection and no escape at door.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $485 total. Same-day, completed on the diagnostic visit in 2 hours.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Gaggenau DF 480 dishwasher, Holmby Hills</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Door not staying open at partial-release positions — slamming down or drifting open mid-load. Custom panel showing a slight off-axis catch against the surrounding cabinetry. Unit was 5 years old.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> 2017-2021 DF 480 door spring assembly failure pattern. Both springs out of spec on tension test — the right side was the visible failure but the left side measured within 15% of failure threshold.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Door spring assembly replaced as a paired set (both sides, OEM Gaggenau parts pre-staged from BSH USA Irvine on phone-identified symptoms). Verified door balance at full and partial-open positions. Re-aligned custom panel to remove the off-axis catch. Gap lines verified consistent.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $485 total (paired-set parts cost + alignment labor). Same-day, 90 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Gaggenau BS 484 full-steam oven, Trousdale Estates</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Steam cycles getting noticeably longer than the owner remembered, water reservoir filling more often. Descale prompt on the front panel had been dismissed multiple times over 14 months.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Calcium scale buildup in the steam-generation system from missed descale interval. LA hard-water service area (Beverly Hills LADWP supply) — 6-month interval applies, not the 12-month manual default. Boiler element output measured 30% below spec, consistent with scale-restricted flow but not yet element-failure territory.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Full descale cycle using OEM Gaggenau descaler (manufacturer-approved agent, not third-party citric-acid substitute). Verified normal water flow through steam-generation system after descale. Boiler element output restored to spec — no element replacement needed. Documented 6-month descale cadence for the owner going forward.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $325 total. Same-day, 90 minutes on-site. Would have been $580-$880 if descale hadn't been run first and element replacement had been quoted blind.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

